getInstanceGroup

private List<Scope> getInstanceGroup()
In the case of scope specific compensation (compensateScope), the Compensation Handler Instance Group contains the installed compensation handler instances of a particular target scope that is executed within a repeatable construct.

If a scope being compensated by name is nested in a while, repeatUntil, or non-parallel forEach loop, the invocation of the installed instances of the compensation handlers in the successive iterations MUST be in reverse order.

In the case of parallel and event handlers, no ordering requirement is imposed on the compensation of the associated scope.

Returns:
All instances of the target scope.
